♫ We have chop suey
every Thursday noon ♫

17
00:05:44.945 --> 00:05:46.679
Man: Salisbury steaks
in brown gravy.

18
00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:50.417
A new frozen main dish.
A taste of home.

19
00:05:50.418 --> 00:05:54.021
Your own shooting gallery?
You bet. with the...

20
00:05:56.424 --> 00:05:57.924
The United States continues

21
00:05:57.925 --> 00:06:00.126
to reinforce its Cuban base
at Guantanamo Bay.

22
00:06:00.127 --> 00:06:03.796
the naval depot that Castro
wants the U.S. to give up.

23
00:06:03.797 --> 00:06:05.432
These marines have
been assigned the job

24
00:06:05.433 --> 00:06:07.266
of protecting the base
against any Cuban threats

25
00:06:07.267 --> 00:06:09.802
that might arise during
the present crisis.

26
00:06:09.803 --> 00:06:12.304
They'll be on 24-hour alert...

27
00:06:12.305 --> 00:06:15.174
Our first line of defense.

28
00:07:05.659 --> 00:07:07.494
I hear you've been
looking for me.

29
00:07:07.495 --> 00:07:09.028
I'm George Dixon.

30
00:07:09.029 --> 00:07:11.230
I disconnected the
microphones in your room

31
00:07:11.231 --> 00:07:13.700
and the tap on the phone
so we can talk.

32
00:07:13.701 --> 00:07:15.535
But they can still see you.

33
00:07:15.536 --> 00:07:17.837
Who is able to see me?

34
00:07:17.838 --> 00:07:20.540
You really should not
have come here.

35
00:07:20.541 --> 00:07:22.008
Listen. I came here to find you.

36
00:07:22.009 --> 00:07:23.543
My mom told me be the truth
about you and Trudy.

37
00:07:23.544 --> 00:07:26.546
You betrayed everything
she died for.

38
00:07:26.547 --> 00:07:28.048
You're Resistance.

39
00:07:29.182 --> 00:07:30.850
Those men who just
tried to kill me.

40
00:07:30.851 --> 00:07:32.351
- are they with you?
- Since Trudy loved you.

41
00:07:32.352 --> 00:07:34.787
I'm going to give you
this advice just once.

42
00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:38.691
Run away. far away.

43
00:07:38.692 --> 00:07:41.127
We will never forget
what you did.

44
00:07:41.128 --> 00:07:42.962
- Don't hang up.
- Goodbye. Juliana.

45
00:07:42.963 --> 00:07:45.198
The Man in the High
Castle sent me.

46
00:07:48.969 --> 00:07:49.969
Hello?

47
00:07:51.539 --> 00:07:52.806
Hello.

48
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:58.645
Tomorrow 8 a.m.

49
00:07:58.646 --> 00:08:00.980
Walk west into Central Park.

50
00:08:00.981 --> 00:08:02.715
past the Chancellor's Museum

51
00:08:02.716 --> 00:08:05.351
towards the lake
at East 79th Street.

52
00:08:05.352 --> 00:08:08.020
- You got it?
- Yes.

53
00:08:08.021 --> 00:08:09.656
How will I find you?

54
00:08:09.657 --> 00:08:11.191
I'll find you.

55
00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:27.274
Sit beside me.

56
00:08:42.590 --> 00:08:43.923
Why here?

57
00:08:43.924 --> 00:08:47.294
I don't want to end up
in a Gestapo basement.

58
00:08:51.331 --> 00:08:53.233
I'm not a Nazi.

59
00:08:54.467 --> 00:08:56.202
Did you or did you not

60
00:08:56.203 --> 00:08:59.739
give Joe Blake the film
and let him escape?

61
00:08:59.740 --> 00:09:02.009
Not for the reasons you think.

62
00:09:03.744 --> 00:09:05.444
So it's coincidence
you're sponsored

63
00:09:05.445 --> 00:09:08.347
by the most evil
son of a bitch
in the American Reich.

64
00:09:08.348 --> 00:09:09.749
What are you talking about?

65
00:09:09.750 --> 00:09:11.652
John Smith.

66
00:09:12.620 --> 00:09:14.420
Do you know how many people

67
00:09:14.421 --> 00:09:16.056
he's had killed?

68
00:09:17.190 --> 00:09:18.825
No. I just met him.

69
00:09:18.826 --> 00:09:20.927
I don't know what he
wants from me. either.

70
00:09:20.928 --> 00:09:22.962
Well. he didn't grant you asylum

71
00:09:22.963 --> 00:09:25.132
out of the kindness
of his own heart.

72
00:09:26.634 --> 00:09:28.367
I'm guessing
it has something to do

73
00:09:28.368 --> 00:09:30.904
with the Man you mentioned.

74
00:09:39.479 --> 00:09:41.447
You're in his films. George.

75
00:09:41.448 --> 00:09:43.249
What the hell
are you talking about?

76
00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:46.185
In one of them.
San Francisco's destroyed

77
00:09:46.186 --> 00:09:48.120
by an atomic blast.

78
00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:50.189
Jesus.

79
00:09:50.190 --> 00:09:52.324
It's part of why I
came to find you.

80
00:09:52.325 --> 00:09:55.327
He thinks you've
got something to do
with causing it.

81
00:09:55.328 --> 00:09:57.496
Me? How?

82
00:09:57.497 --> 00:09:58.898
I don't know.

83
00:09:58.899 --> 00:10:01.201
- Why?
- I don't know.

84
00:10:03.270 --> 00:10:05.905
San Francisco is my home.

85
00:10:05.906 --> 00:10:09.208
I hate the Pons. but I want
to go back there one day.

86
00:10:09.209 --> 00:10:11.010
There are people there
that I love.

87
00:10:11.011 --> 00:10:12.879
So you can't think
of any reason why...

88
00:10:12.880 --> 00:10:14.714
No. Of course not.

89
00:10:14.715 --> 00:10:16.983
If I thought for a second
that he was right.

90
00:10:16.984 --> 00:10:21.154
I'd... I'd put a bullet
in my own head.

91
00:10:23.323 --> 00:10:26.125
Then maybe this is enough:

92
00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:27.393
me warning you.

93
00:10:27.394 --> 00:10:29.161
Maybe this is enough
to stop it happening.

94
00:10:29.162 --> 00:10:31.630
If he wanted to talk to me.
he knows where I am.

95
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:32.932
Why would he send you?

96
00:10:32.933 --> 00:10:36.336
He didn't exactly send me.

97
00:10:39.873 --> 00:10:41.741
Look. he knew that I knew you

98
00:10:41.742 --> 00:10:43.711
from his films somehow. but...

99
00:10:45.312 --> 00:10:47.747
Listen. my mom told me
the truth about you and Trudy.

100
00:10:47.748 --> 00:10:49.015
but I just had this feeling.

101
00:10:49.016 --> 00:10:50.349
and I knew it had to be
me who found you.

102
00:10:50.350 --> 00:10:54.287
that... this is all
happening for a reason.

103
00:10:57.024 --> 00:10:59.025
That's really why you came here?

104
00:10:59.026 --> 00:11:01.328
You have to believe me.

105
00:11:07.367 --> 00:11:09.002
Juliana: George.

106
00:11:10.137 --> 00:11:11.171
George?

107
00:11:15.508 --> 00:11:17.077
It's okay.

108
00:11:27.620 --> 00:11:29.289
Don't make me regret this.

109
00:11:30.590 --> 00:11:31.791
Let's go.

110
00:11:31.792 --> 00:11:33.961
- Where?
- You'll find out.

111
00:11:48.341 --> 00:11:49.508
Girl: Hello.

112
00:11:49.509 --> 00:11:51.043
- Annie?
- Yes.

113
00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:53.980
It... Yeah. it's Thomas.

114
00:11:53.981 --> 00:11:57.483
I tried to find you
after school yesterday.

115
00:11:57.484 --> 00:12:00.386
I heard you're going
to the mixer with Barker?

116
00:12:01.454 --> 00:12:03.790
He asked me yesterday
after school.

117
00:12:05.592 --> 00:12:08.627
Yeah. That's okay.
I understand.

118
00:12:08.628 --> 00:12:11.597
He's. uh.
really athletic and all.

119
00:12:11.598 --> 00:12:13.032
Tommy's in love.

120
00:12:13.033 --> 00:12:16.202
Tommy and Annie.
sitting in a tree.

121
00:12:16.203 --> 00:12:18.570
K-I-S-S-I-N-G.

122
00:12:18.571 --> 00:12:19.839
That's enough.

123
00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:21.173
Thomas. are you there?

124
00:12:21.174 --> 00:12:22.976
- Gotta go. Bye.
- Thomas?

125
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:26.012
I'm sorry. Mother.

126
00:12:26.013 --> 00:12:29.282
Don't be sorry.
Just have a seat. please.

127
00:12:32.685 --> 00:12:34.553
Tommy's in love.

128
00:12:34.554 --> 00:12:35.554
Shut up.

129
00:12:36.656 --> 00:12:38.191
Did I just hear "Shut up"?

130
00:12:39.359 --> 00:12:42.228
Sorry. Father.
Jennifer was teasing me.

131
00:12:42.229 --> 00:12:46.299
No teasing at the table.
please. or anywhere else.

132
00:12:49.669 --> 00:12:51.904
Thomas.
is that a little peach fuzz

133
00:12:51.905 --> 00:12:53.305
I see on that chin of yours?

134
00:12:54.407 --> 00:12:56.442
I have an extra razor
you could use

135
00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:57.509
before we get you your own.

136
00:12:57.510 --> 00:12:59.246
Thank you. Father.

137
00:13:01.949 --> 00:13:04.650
Why don't I cancel
Julia tonight?

138
00:13:04.651 --> 00:13:07.686
Just the family for dinner.

139
00:13:07.687 --> 00:13:09.155
Such short notice.

140
00:13:09.156 --> 00:13:11.158
We don't want to be rude. do we?

141
00:13:12.325 --> 00:13:14.560
I'm sure she's tired
from the move.

142
00:13:14.561 --> 00:13:16.163
Ah. she'll be fine.

143
00:13:17.597 --> 00:13:19.867
Everything will be fine.

144
00:13:31.744 --> 00:13:33.881
- Hey.
- Hey.

145
00:13:35.082 --> 00:13:36.515
Everything go all right?

146
00:13:36.516 --> 00:13:39.251
Yeah. It went fine.
Where's Childan?

147
00:13:39.252 --> 00:13:42.421
Childan's here. left alone.

148
00:13:42.422 --> 00:13:45.892
unpleasantly.
with the Conspiracy King.

149
00:13:45.893 --> 00:13:47.894
You'd be smart to take
that Heydrich tip.

150
00:13:47.895 --> 00:13:49.261
Depending on how that plays out.

151
00:13:49.262 --> 00:13:50.696
it could shift
the power balance.

152
00:13:50.697 --> 00:13:53.032
Yes. well. it's already
shifted my blood pressure

153
00:13:53.033 --> 00:13:55.501
- sharply upward.
- You two work it out.

154
00:13:55.502 --> 00:13:56.702
I'm gonna take a shower.

155
00:13:56.703 --> 00:13:58.171
- clean up.
- Hey.

156
00:13:59.907 --> 00:14:01.673
We need to talk.

157
00:14:01.674 --> 00:14:02.909
What?

158
00:14:02.910 --> 00:14:04.945
Where have you been?

159
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:10.516
Stashing the explosive.

160
00:14:10.517 --> 00:14:12.219
All night?

161
00:14:16.289 --> 00:14:18.824
You have got to be kidding me.

162
00:14:18.825 --> 00:14:20.227
You and that...

163
00:14:24.597 --> 00:14:25.831
So what about the stuff?

164
00:14:25.832 --> 00:14:27.166
What are they gonna do with it?

165
00:14:27.167 --> 00:14:29.969
I didn't ask.
The less we know. the better.

166
00:14:29.970 --> 00:14:31.203
We shouldn't have done
that. Frank.

167
00:14:31.204 --> 00:14:32.404
We should not have helped them.

168
00:14:32.405 --> 00:14:33.940
Come on. Tell me
it didn't feel good.

169
00:14:33.941 --> 00:14:35.741
It didn't.

170
00:14:35.742 --> 00:14:38.311
We're not like those
people. Frank.

171
00:14:39.746 --> 00:14:41.982
Yeah. well. maybe we should be.

172
00:14:45.418 --> 00:14:46.519
Hey.

173
00:14:49.189 --> 00:14:51.591
A little privacy. please?

174
00:15:00.633 --> 00:15:01.634
Danke.

175
00:15:05.205 --> 00:15:06.406
Josef?

176
00:15:08.841 --> 00:15:11.243
I was informed you were leaving.

177
00:15:11.244 --> 00:15:13.379
Have you come
to see me off or stop me?

178
00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:15.081
I will not force you to stay.

179
00:15:15.082 --> 00:15:17.549
but there is something
I need to ask from you.

180
00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:18.717
What's that?

181
00:15:18.718 --> 00:15:20.186
I need you to come with me.

182
00:15:20.187 --> 00:15:21.853
There's something
I need to show you.

183
00:15:21.854 --> 00:15:23.055
My plane leaves at 3.

184
00:15:23.056 --> 00:15:25.057
I won't let it
leave without you.

185
00:15:25.058 --> 00:15:27.994
We'll drop you
at the airport after.

186
00:15:27.995 --> 00:15:29.461
After what?

187
00:15:29.462 --> 00:15:32.331
After you hear the truth.

188
00:15:32.332 --> 00:15:35.534
Please. This is important.

189
00:15:35.535 --> 00:15:39.106
even more important
for you than me.

190
00:15:57.024 --> 00:15:58.757
What is this place?

191
00:15:58.758 --> 00:16:02.561
The Jews built it
as a nursing home
before the war.

192
00:16:02.562 --> 00:16:05.164
A poor investment.

193
00:16:05.165 --> 00:16:08.134
We renamed it
Haus Fruhlingsdammerung:

194
00:16:08.135 --> 00:16:10.503
Spring Dawn House.

195
00:16:27.954 --> 00:16:29.555
We won't be long.

196
00:16:29.556 --> 00:16:31.191
Come this way.

197
00:16:34.294 --> 00:16:37.063
Have you heard
of the term Lebensborn?

198
00:16:37.064 --> 00:16:42.801
No? I think the translation
is. uh. "Fountain of Life."

199
00:16:42.802 --> 00:16:44.436
Yeah. guys in school
used to talk

200
00:16:44.437 --> 00:16:46.338
about those
Fountain of Life places.

201
00:16:46.339 --> 00:16:49.375
Weren't they cat houses for
the top guys in the Reich?

202
00:16:49.376 --> 00:16:51.843
That was a myth about them.

203
00:16:51.844 --> 00:16:54.613
What was.
and indeed remains real.

204
00:16:54.614 --> 00:16:58.751
is the Führer's desire
to perfect the species.

205
00:17:00.153 --> 00:17:02.954
And Lebensborn is...

206
00:17:02.955 --> 00:17:05.624
an early attempt to that end.

207
00:17:05.625 --> 00:17:10.630
I think it... This way.
This way. Ja.

208
00:17:12.199 --> 00:17:16.335
You see. this facility was
phased out in the late '40s

209
00:17:16.336 --> 00:17:20.739
after it failed to deliver
the desired results.

210
00:17:20.740 --> 00:17:22.274
But there are still some

211
00:17:22.275 --> 00:17:24.110
who still see the children
of Lebensborn

212
00:17:24.111 --> 00:17:25.645
as the chosen ones...

213
00:17:27.314 --> 00:17:29.416
the Führer's own offspring.

214
00:17:30.550 --> 00:17:32.851
I guess there's a point
to this. right?

215
00:17:32.852 --> 00:17:34.886
Yes.

216
00:17:34.887 --> 00:17:37.156
Racially desirable women

217
00:17:37.157 --> 00:17:39.325
volunteered to have their babies

218
00:17:39.326 --> 00:17:41.827
at the Lebensborn
birthing houses

219
00:17:41.828 --> 00:17:45.132
to be raised in line
with the Party ideals.

220
00:17:46.933 --> 00:17:48.767
Places like this one

221
00:17:48.768 --> 00:17:54.807
were to provide
the next generation
of the SS elite.

222
00:18:04.851 --> 00:18:07.820
So this was a birthing house.

223
00:18:09.055 --> 00:18:11.157
This was...

224
00:18:11.158 --> 00:18:13.793
your birthing house. Josef.

225
00:18:26.573 --> 00:18:28.307
What the hell are you
talking about?

226
00:18:28.308 --> 00:18:32.944
You were born here
on April 10. 1935.

227
00:18:32.945 --> 00:18:35.448
at 7:32 in the morning.

228
00:18:37.284 --> 00:18:39.185
No. I wasn't.

229
00:18:39.186 --> 00:18:40.486
On August the following year.

230
00:18:40.487 --> 00:18:42.288
you were kidnapped
and taken to America.

231
00:18:42.289 --> 00:18:45.424
No. I was born in Brooklyn
in a filthy hovel

232
00:18:45.425 --> 00:18:48.360
that
my mother couldn't afford
because you abandoned us.

233
00:18:48.361 --> 00:18:50.296
I'm sorry.
That simply isn't true.

234
00:18:50.297 --> 00:18:52.764
I understand how
upsetting this must be.

235
00:18:52.765 --> 00:18:54.733
You don't understand
a thing about me.

236
00:18:54.734 --> 00:18:56.302
When Elsa stole you.

237
00:18:56.303 --> 00:18:58.637
I wanted her caught
and you brought back.

238
00:18:58.638 --> 00:19:00.472
But I came to realize
this program was wrong.

239
00:19:00.473 --> 00:19:03.275
Its intentions were pure.
but its methods were cruel.

240
00:19:03.276 --> 00:19:04.643
I don't believe
a word you're saying!

241
00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:06.878
Your mother was right
to take you away. Josef.

242
00:19:06.879 --> 00:19:08.013
You must never blame her.

243
00:19:08.014 --> 00:19:09.582
Stay the hell away from me.

244
00:19:59.866 --> 00:20:00.932
Yes. Sergeant.

245
00:20:00.933 --> 00:20:02.301
Sir.

246
00:20:02.302 --> 00:20:04.503
our agents have located
Juliana Crain in New York

247
00:20:04.504 --> 00:20:06.037
and are making arrangements.

248
00:20:06.038 --> 00:20:09.408
Inform them I want her
brought back immediately.

249
00:20:09.409 --> 00:20:12.645
Sir. it may be more
complicated than we thought.

250
00:20:23.323 --> 00:20:25.257
Her asylum is being
personally sponsored

251
00:20:25.258 --> 00:20:26.926
by Obergruppenführer Smith.

252
00:20:31.698 --> 00:20:33.699
That is...

253
00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:35.868
very troubling.

254
00:20:37.737 --> 00:20:40.239
Do we proceed with
the operation anyway?

255
00:21:07.467 --> 00:21:12.338
The Nazis keep jamming
the usual frequency.

256
00:21:12.339 --> 00:21:16.007
but they broadcast
on a secondary...

257
00:21:28.220 --> 00:21:29.755
Juliana:
What kind of music is this?

258
00:21:29.756 --> 00:21:33.759
It's Pirate Radio.
from the Neutral Zone.

259
00:21:33.760 --> 00:21:37.563
A little reminder of
what we're fighting for.

260
00:21:37.564 --> 00:21:40.532
Unlike any music
I've ever heard.

261
00:21:40.533 --> 00:21:42.267
That's because it's illegal.

262
00:21:42.268 --> 00:21:45.537
Too much of the Negro influence.

263
00:21:45.538 --> 00:21:47.906
So don't tune in at home

264
00:21:47.907 --> 00:21:49.609
if you don't want
the Nazis listening.

265
00:21:55.948 --> 00:21:56.849
You wouldn't know it.

266
00:21:56.850 --> 00:21:58.685
but this
used to be a great city...

267
00:22:00.152 --> 00:22:01.654
before.

268
00:22:02.822 --> 00:22:06.392
It was noisy and a little messy

269
00:22:06.393 --> 00:22:08.394
but...

270
00:22:08.395 --> 00:22:10.530
totally alive.

271
00:22:11.531 --> 00:22:13.465
San Francisco. too.

272
00:22:13.466 --> 00:22:16.568
You're too young
to remember. aren't you?

273
00:22:16.569 --> 00:22:18.770
I remember looking out
the window with Trudy.

274
00:22:18.771 --> 00:22:21.641
watching the Japanese tanks
rolling down the Embarcadero.

275
00:22:24.744 --> 00:22:26.845
How did she get here?

276
00:22:26.846 --> 00:22:28.948
Into the Reich.

277
00:22:32.719 --> 00:22:35.153
I don't want to talk
about Trudy.
Why not?

278
00:22:35.154 --> 00:22:37.889
Because she worshiped
the ground you walked on.

279
00:22:37.890 --> 00:22:39.425
After what you did.

280
00:22:39.426 --> 00:22:41.192
even she couldn't forgive you.

281
00:22:41.193 --> 00:22:43.128
If you think you knew
my sister better than I did.

282
00:22:43.129 --> 00:22:44.129
you're wrong.

283
00:22:45.632 --> 00:22:47.232
Here's the deal. kiddo.

284
00:22:47.233 --> 00:22:49.601
Your father and I
were best friends.

285
00:22:49.602 --> 00:22:52.838
Your mother and I were...

286
00:22:52.839 --> 00:22:54.105
close.

287
00:22:54.106 --> 00:22:57.008
So I don't want your blood
on my hands.

288
00:22:57.009 --> 00:22:58.043
What does that mean?

289
00:22:58.044 --> 00:23:00.679
My people want you dead
for what you did.

290
00:23:00.680 --> 00:23:02.581
You sent them away.

291
00:23:02.582 --> 00:23:04.550
Well. I'm not in charge.

292
00:23:04.551 --> 00:23:06.552
The only reason they're
letting me talk to you

293
00:23:06.553 --> 00:23:07.819
is to give you a chance.

294
00:23:07.820 --> 00:23:09.756
- Chance to what?
- Redeem yourself.

295
00:23:11.123 --> 00:23:13.525
Look. George. I can't
get the film back.

296
00:23:13.526 --> 00:23:15.894
Oh. they know that.

297
00:23:15.895 --> 00:23:18.930
Then what do they want from me?

298
00:23:26.573 --> 00:23:28.640
Tell me this isn't about Smith.

299
00:23:28.641 --> 00:23:31.076
He's our top target.

300
00:23:31.077 --> 00:23:33.512
We've come close. but...

301
00:23:33.513 --> 00:23:35.747
I'm not an assassin. George.

302
00:23:35.748 --> 00:23:37.883
Nobody's asking you
to do that...

303
00:23:37.884 --> 00:23:40.186
Not right now. at any rate.

304
00:23:48.060 --> 00:23:50.162
I don't know what you
think I can do.

305
00:23:51.798 --> 00:23:54.866
We want you to get close to
the Smiths and their friends.

306
00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:55.967
Why?

307
00:23:55.968 --> 00:23:58.403
Because my people
are telling you to.

308
00:23:58.404 --> 00:24:00.972
Look. you don't understand.
They're playing at something.

309
00:24:00.973 --> 00:24:02.508
They don't actually trust me.

310
00:24:02.509 --> 00:24:04.309
Go figure.

311
00:24:04.310 --> 00:24:07.012
Look. you tell your people
that this isn't going to work.

312
00:24:07.013 --> 00:24:08.514
You understand?

313
00:24:08.515 --> 00:24:10.582
You really want me to do that?

314
00:24:10.583 --> 00:24:13.251
Because it's the deal
I struck with them

315
00:24:13.252 --> 00:24:15.722
to keep them from killing you.

316
00:24:21.928 --> 00:24:24.096
I think I'm going to be sick.

317
00:24:26.098 --> 00:24:28.535
You really shouldn't
have helped that Nazi.

318
00:25:11.578 --> 00:25:13.580
Did you ever love her?

319
00:25:15.014 --> 00:25:16.715
Or was she just breeding stock?

320
00:25:16.716 --> 00:25:18.651
Oh. I loved your mother.

321
00:25:19.886 --> 00:25:24.190
And I was very proud
of my first son.

322
00:25:26.225 --> 00:25:27.760
Why didn't she tell me?

323
00:25:29.028 --> 00:25:31.830
If she had told you the truth.

324
00:25:31.831 --> 00:25:34.233
how would you
have reacted? Hmm?

325
00:25:36.636 --> 00:25:38.336
My whole life is a lie.

326
00:25:38.337 --> 00:25:41.239
Hmm.
No. no. no. no. no.

327
00:25:41.240 --> 00:25:44.142
Your actions define you.

328
00:25:44.143 --> 00:25:46.144
And they do not lie.

329
00:25:46.145 --> 00:25:50.048
I am proud of the man
that you have become.

330
00:25:50.049 --> 00:25:51.984
And who is that?

331
00:25:56.155 --> 00:25:57.488
Who have I become?

332
00:25:57.489 --> 00:26:01.026
You are a good man.

333
00:26:01.027 --> 00:26:05.097
worthy of my trust. Josef.

334
00:26:07.066 --> 00:26:11.202
There is a world of
possibilities here for you.

335
00:26:11.203 --> 00:26:12.672
if you want them.

336
00:26:13.640 --> 00:26:16.007
I want very much
for you to stay.

337
00:26:16.008 --> 00:26:19.645
but if you prefer
to go to New York.

338
00:26:19.646 --> 00:26:21.747
I understand.

339
00:26:21.748 --> 00:26:24.183
And I will no longer interfere.

340
00:26:47.940 --> 00:26:50.076
Oh. hey. what's going on?

341
00:26:52.879 --> 00:26:54.680
I got your message.

342
00:26:54.681 --> 00:26:57.048
Come in and find out.

343
00:26:57.049 --> 00:26:58.217
How's Ed?

344
00:26:59.285 --> 00:27:00.986
I kind of like Ed.

345
00:27:00.987 --> 00:27:04.589
Oh. yeah? Uh. well. yeah.
he likes you. too.

346
00:27:04.590 --> 00:27:08.459
Frank. you did good yesterday.

347
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:09.795
Want a beer?

348
00:27:09.796 --> 00:27:10.997
Nah. no thanks.

349
00:27:12.331 --> 00:27:14.432
So you know what you're
going to do with it?

350
00:27:14.433 --> 00:27:16.267
The explosive?

351
00:27:16.268 --> 00:27:18.704
Not your problem.

352
00:27:18.705 --> 00:27:22.507
But it won't go
to waste. Trust me.

353
00:27:22.508 --> 00:27:24.376
Yeah. I trust you.

354
00:27:25.611 --> 00:27:27.713
- You all right?
- Yeah.

355
00:27:27.714 --> 00:27:29.247
Can I talk to you for a second?

356
00:27:29.248 --> 00:27:30.382
- Yeah.
- Okay.

357
00:27:31.583 --> 00:27:33.084
I really feel like. uh.

358
00:27:33.085 --> 00:27:35.186
like I should be there.
you know?

359
00:27:35.187 --> 00:27:37.422
We both know where you
need to be right now.

360
00:27:37.423 --> 00:27:39.624
You're the only one
standing between him and...

361
00:27:39.625 --> 00:27:41.293
Yeah. I know. I know.

362
00:27:44.230 --> 00:27:45.530
Leave this for me.

363
00:27:45.531 --> 00:27:46.564
Yeah.

364
00:27:46.565 --> 00:27:47.733
Okay.

365
00:27:47.734 --> 00:27:49.034
Look out for yourself. brother.

366
00:27:49.035 --> 00:27:50.268
All right. You. too.

367
00:27:50.269 --> 00:27:51.636
Sara.

368
00:27:51.637 --> 00:27:53.405
Be safe.

369
00:28:08.454 --> 00:28:10.655
So what are we doing here?

370
00:28:10.656 --> 00:28:12.291
What does it look like. Frank?

371
00:28:13.525 --> 00:28:15.027
Wetting my whistle.

372
00:28:17.429 --> 00:28:20.231
There's something I need
to ask you about.

373
00:28:20.232 --> 00:28:21.801
Shoot.

374
00:28:23.369 --> 00:28:25.570
The films.

375
00:28:25.571 --> 00:28:27.439
I need to know about them.

376
00:28:30.142 --> 00:28:31.209
Why?

377
00:28:31.210 --> 00:28:33.913
Because I saw the one
that Juliana...

378
00:28:36.648 --> 00:28:39.017
Because I saw myself die in it.

379
00:28:39.018 --> 00:28:40.852
You were in the film?

380
00:28:40.853 --> 00:28:42.789
Yeah. I was in...

381
00:28:44.623 --> 00:28:48.995
I. uh. saw myself...
get executed.

382
00:28:50.529 --> 00:28:51.797
Then you know everything

383
00:28:51.798 --> 00:28:53.631
you need to know
about the films.

384
00:28:53.632 --> 00:28:55.901
why we don't fucking watch them.

385
00:28:55.902 --> 00:28:59.805
I was on my knees.
It never happened.

386
00:28:59.806 --> 00:29:01.172
How could they have a film...

387
00:29:01.173 --> 00:29:03.809
Ted Vecchione. 1947.
Bobby Vecchione. 1949.

388
00:29:03.810 --> 00:29:09.816
Sam Kyle...
Karen's husband. 1961.

389
00:29:11.383 --> 00:29:12.985
And now Karen herself...

390
00:29:14.053 --> 00:29:17.023
The last of the Vecchione
family. 1962.

391
00:29:18.557 --> 00:29:19.825
What are you talking about?

392
00:29:19.826 --> 00:29:21.192
I'm talking about the fact

393
00:29:21.193 --> 00:29:23.094
that it doesn't matter
what you saw on those films.

394
00:29:23.095 --> 00:29:25.363
We're all going to die.

395
00:29:25.364 --> 00:29:28.366
The question is. do you
want to die on your knees

396
00:29:28.367 --> 00:29:30.837
or do you want to die
standing tall?

397
00:29:33.039 --> 00:29:35.041
We have to go.

398
00:29:35.942 --> 00:29:37.844
Come with us.

399
00:29:57.363 --> 00:29:59.497
He came alone?

400
00:29:59.498 --> 00:30:01.266
No appointment?

401
00:30:01.267 --> 00:30:02.401
Yes. sir.

402
00:30:13.745 --> 00:30:15.982
Chief Inspector Kido.

403
00:30:19.886 --> 00:30:22.488
I am Obergruppenführer Smith.

404
00:30:23.689 --> 00:30:25.191
Obergruppenführer.

405
00:30:27.626 --> 00:30:29.460
To what do we owe the pleasure?

406
00:30:29.461 --> 00:30:33.131
I come on the orders
of General Onoda

407
00:30:33.132 --> 00:30:35.034
with a request.

408
00:30:41.607 --> 00:30:45.945
For the extradition
of Juliana Crain.

409
00:30:55.387 --> 00:30:56.622
Please come in.

410
00:30:59.591 --> 00:31:01.960
Well. this is a...

411
00:31:01.961 --> 00:31:05.997
it's a little awkward.
I must say. Chief Inspector.

412
00:31:05.998 --> 00:31:09.400
You see. Juliana Crain

413
00:31:09.401 --> 00:31:13.171
has been granted
asylum here in the Reich.

414
00:31:13.172 --> 00:31:15.140
But when that decision was made.

415
00:31:15.141 --> 00:31:19.344
the Reich may not have been in
possession of all the facts.

416
00:31:19.345 --> 00:31:20.412
No?

417
00:31:22.414 --> 00:31:23.482
Please take a seat.

418
00:31:31.357 --> 00:31:35.060
Miss Crain is a known
member of the Resistance.

419
00:31:35.061 --> 00:31:39.630
She was involved in the murder
of two of my officers.

420
00:31:39.631 --> 00:31:42.968
We interviewed Miss Crain.

421
00:31:42.969 --> 00:31:46.104
I'm satisfied she was never
a member of the Resistance.

422
00:31:46.105 --> 00:31:48.439
In fact. she sought refuge here

423
00:31:48.440 --> 00:31:50.108
because the Resistance
is trying to kill her.

424
00:31:50.109 --> 00:31:52.343
Yes. because she betrayed them

425
00:31:52.344 --> 00:31:56.548
after they brought her to meet
the Man in the High Castle.

426
00:32:00.786 --> 00:32:02.654
You have proof of this?

427
00:32:10.329 --> 00:32:13.098
Erich. could you. uh.

428
00:32:13.099 --> 00:32:14.366
could you give us a moment?

429
00:32:25.877 --> 00:32:29.180
The medal behind your desk.

430
00:32:29.181 --> 00:32:32.218
Might I examine it more closely?

431
00:32:37.756 --> 00:32:39.025
Be my guest.

432
00:32:49.101 --> 00:32:51.137
The Solomon Islands.

433
00:32:53.772 --> 00:32:58.044
Why display a medal from
your U.S. military service?

434
00:33:00.046 --> 00:33:02.181
I keep it as a reminder.

435
00:33:04.216 --> 00:33:09.055
The consequences
of the failure of command.

436
00:33:16.828 --> 00:33:21.067
There were many casualties
in that campaign.

437
00:33:24.070 --> 00:33:26.172
On both sides.

438
00:33:29.675 --> 00:33:31.509
You were there?

439
00:33:31.510 --> 00:33:35.747
Yes. Obergruppenführer.

440
00:33:39.818 --> 00:33:41.253
I was.

441
00:33:56.602 --> 00:34:00.306
Tell me something.
Chief Inspector.

442
00:34:02.774 --> 00:34:04.410
Soldier to soldier.

443
00:34:09.115 --> 00:34:11.249
You must have known
before you came here

444
00:34:11.250 --> 00:34:13.119
I was going to refuse
your extradition request.

445
00:34:17.123 --> 00:34:19.191
Why are you really here?

446
00:34:49.221 --> 00:34:50.821
Sir. if I may ask...

447
00:34:50.822 --> 00:34:52.491
Listen to me. Erich.

448
00:34:54.393 --> 00:34:58.663
I want you to erase
all record of that meeting

449
00:34:58.664 --> 00:34:59.831
from the log.

450
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:03.169
Understand?

451
00:35:05.171 --> 00:35:07.206
He was never here.

452
00:36:15.574 --> 00:36:16.874
Hello.

453
00:36:16.875 --> 00:36:18.343
Good day. Miss Mills.

454
00:36:18.344 --> 00:36:20.378
It's John Smith.

455
00:36:20.379 --> 00:36:21.546
Well. hello.

456
00:36:21.547 --> 00:36:23.113
Did I catch you at a bad time?

457
00:36:23.114 --> 00:36:24.449
No. no. no.

458
00:36:24.450 --> 00:36:26.651
I've just been doing
a little house cleaning.

459
00:36:26.652 --> 00:36:28.919
Cleanliness is a virtue
here in the Reich.

460
00:36:28.920 --> 00:36:31.256
Yes. Yes. I read that.

461
00:36:31.257 --> 00:36:32.690
Glad you're fitting in.

462
00:36:32.691 --> 00:36:34.359
Helen wanted me to ask you

463
00:36:34.360 --> 00:36:36.527
if you have any
objection to pot roast.

464
00:36:36.528 --> 00:36:38.529
- Pot roast?
- For dinner tonight.

465
00:36:38.530 --> 00:36:40.465
That is if you
can still make it?

466
00:36:40.466 --> 00:36:44.001
Right. Uh. pot roast
is wonderful.

467
00:36:44.002 --> 00:36:45.603
Is there anything I can bring?

468
00:36:45.604 --> 00:36:48.273
No. just yourself.
See you at 7.

469
00:36:48.274 --> 00:36:49.808
See you then.

470
00:38:14.693 --> 00:38:17.362
Man: Mutual assured
destruction

471
00:38:17.363 --> 00:38:18.796
is what McNarmara calls it.

472
00:38:18.797 --> 00:38:21.899
And I say. damn right it is.

473
00:38:21.900 --> 00:38:24.101
Woman: Never thought
I'd look back

474
00:38:24.102 --> 00:38:25.636
on the world wars as quaint.

475
00:38:25.637 --> 00:38:26.904
How's Tina taking it?

476
00:38:26.905 --> 00:38:29.073
She must be scared
out of her wits.

477
00:38:29.074 --> 00:38:30.508
My Tina. she's in fourth grade.

478
00:38:30.509 --> 00:38:32.377
and they have her doing
duck-and-cover exercises

479
00:38:32.378 --> 00:38:33.544
every single day.

480
00:38:33.545 --> 00:38:35.880
Tell that to Nikita Khrushchev.

481
00:38:35.881 --> 00:38:38.248
If you ask me. this
wouldn't be happening

482
00:38:38.249 --> 00:38:42.387
if Eisenhower had let him go
to Disneyland back in '59.

483
00:38:42.388 --> 00:38:43.654
like he wanted.

484
00:38:43.655 --> 00:38:45.022
Well. I don't know about that.

485
00:38:45.023 --> 00:38:46.991
but I'll tell you.
I can't sleep at night.

486
00:38:46.992 --> 00:38:48.726
And I've tried everything:

487
00:38:48.727 --> 00:38:51.462
yoga. deep breathing. wine.

488
00:40:24.523 --> 00:40:25.923
Danke.

489
00:40:31.697 --> 00:40:35.199
Josef. this is Sylvia.

490
00:40:35.200 --> 00:40:38.569
She has looked after our
family since I was a boy.

491
00:40:50.582 --> 00:40:52.249
Danke.

492
00:40:52.250 --> 00:40:54.185
Guten Tag. Fräulein Silvia.

493
00:40:56.522 --> 00:40:58.223
Heil Hitler.

494
00:41:29.755 --> 00:41:31.923
The owner's away.
We're closed.

495
00:41:34.192 --> 00:41:35.827
Yes. I know.

496
00:41:39.565 --> 00:41:40.931
What are you...

497
00:41:40.932 --> 00:41:43.000
Mr. Childan could
be back any second.

498
00:41:43.001 --> 00:41:46.071
You missed our meeting.
Mr. McCarthy.

499
00:41:47.272 --> 00:41:50.075
I know. I couldn't get away.

500
00:41:51.910 --> 00:41:55.212
We continue to let you live
and your friend Frank live.

501
00:41:55.213 --> 00:41:56.582
Why?

502
00:41:58.650 --> 00:42:00.785
So I can be useful.

503
00:42:00.786 --> 00:42:03.153
And are you being useful?

504
00:42:03.154 --> 00:42:05.055
I told you about
the counterfeiting.

505
00:42:05.056 --> 00:42:06.257
That's all I know.

506
00:42:10.295 --> 00:42:14.198
The Yakuza's dealings are
of particular interest to us.

507
00:42:14.199 --> 00:42:15.733
You think they are going
to tell me anything?

508
00:42:15.734 --> 00:42:16.902
A gaijin?

509
00:42:19.270 --> 00:42:21.239
When do you make your
first payment to them?

510
00:42:23.341 --> 00:42:25.911
Soon. I hope.
In a few days.

511
00:42:27.913 --> 00:42:30.480
You will report directly
to me after that meeting.

512
00:42:30.481 --> 00:42:33.250
You will recount every detail.

513
00:42:33.251 --> 00:42:34.852
And then we will decide

514
00:42:34.853 --> 00:42:37.656
if you're continuing
to be useful.

515
00:42:39.658 --> 00:42:41.626
I will. I swear.

516
00:42:41.627 --> 00:42:43.829
Now could you please...

517
00:43:28.306 --> 00:43:30.241
Looks nice.

518
00:43:31.777 --> 00:43:33.745
I didn't hear you come in.

519
00:43:35.747 --> 00:43:40.085
I was just saying...
it looks nice.

520
00:43:41.152 --> 00:43:43.453
Well. hopefully
our guest will think so.

521
00:43:43.454 --> 00:43:48.359
since clearly she is
the most important thing
in our lives right now.

522
00:43:51.930 --> 00:43:53.031
Helen.

523
00:43:56.267 --> 00:43:57.302
What did I say?

524
00:43:59.871 --> 00:44:01.505
I'm taking care of it.

525
00:44:01.506 --> 00:44:03.809
Trust me.

526
00:44:06.712 --> 00:44:08.246
I'll go check the roast.

527
00:44:13.318 --> 00:44:14.385
Thomas: I'll get it.

528
00:44:19.457 --> 00:44:22.092
Hi. Miss Mills.

529
00:44:22.093 --> 00:44:23.227
Hello. Thomas.

530
00:44:23.228 --> 00:44:25.462
I thought we agreed
you'd call me Julia.

531
00:44:25.463 --> 00:44:27.531
I don't think I'm supposed to.

532
00:44:27.532 --> 00:44:28.866
Oh. you're an adult now. Thomas.

533
00:44:28.867 --> 00:44:30.434
I think it should be fine.

534
00:44:30.435 --> 00:44:31.802
Julia. welcome.

535
00:44:31.803 --> 00:44:34.204
Thank you for having me.
Obergruppenführer.

536
00:44:34.205 --> 00:44:36.373
No. no. no. no.
In my home I'm John.

537
00:44:36.374 --> 00:44:38.744
John. Thank you.

538
00:44:39.577 --> 00:44:41.011
Hello. Julia.

539
00:44:41.012 --> 00:44:42.747
Oh. and what are those?

540
00:44:42.748 --> 00:44:44.149
These are for you.

541
00:44:45.316 --> 00:44:47.484
Wow. Beautiful.

542
00:44:47.485 --> 00:44:49.353
Oh. my girls.
Amy. Jennifer.

543
00:44:49.354 --> 00:44:51.221
- This is Miss Mills.
- Hello.

544
00:44:51.222 --> 00:44:53.657
Jennifer. be a dear put that
in a vase with some water.

545
00:44:53.658 --> 00:44:54.825
Please. come through.

546
00:44:54.826 --> 00:44:56.361
We'll put them on the table.

547
00:45:40.638 --> 00:45:42.472
Frank: What is this?

548
00:45:42.473 --> 00:45:44.374
It's a memorial...

549
00:45:44.375 --> 00:45:46.143
for Karen.

550
00:45:46.144 --> 00:45:48.813
There are people here from
the state of Washington.

551
00:45:48.814 --> 00:45:50.816
Baja. the Salt Lake.

552
00:45:55.286 --> 00:45:56.487
Come on.

553
00:46:10.869 --> 00:46:12.669
Man: As we gather tonight.

554
00:46:12.670 --> 00:46:17.207
we remember that the Lord
is close to the brokenhearted

555
00:46:17.208 --> 00:46:21.111
and saves those that
are crushed in spirit.

556
00:46:21.112 --> 00:46:25.082
Remember too. that we
are of good courage

557
00:46:25.083 --> 00:46:27.852
and would rather be
away from the body

558
00:46:27.853 --> 00:46:29.453
and at home with the Lord

559
00:46:29.454 --> 00:46:33.024
surrounded by the loved ones
who went before us.

560
00:46:41.199 --> 00:46:45.002
Of course. the Lord can see
Karen. even though we cannot.

561
00:46:45.003 --> 00:46:47.872
For precious
in the sight of the Lord

562
00:46:47.873 --> 00:46:50.007
is the death of his saints.

563
00:46:50.008 --> 00:46:53.978
So let us lay this
saint to rest.

564
00:46:53.979 --> 00:46:56.446
And let us not linger. children.

565
00:46:56.447 --> 00:47:00.185
for the wolves will soon
be upon our door.

566
00:47:06.925 --> 00:47:08.526
You're one of us now.

567
00:47:34.652 --> 00:47:36.653
The pot roast is delicious.

568
00:47:36.654 --> 00:47:38.788
Mm. Very good.

569
00:47:38.789 --> 00:47:41.058
Why. thank you.

570
00:47:41.059 --> 00:47:42.993
You know. this
tastes a little bit

571
00:47:42.994 --> 00:47:44.929
like pickled cabbage.
is that right?

572
00:47:44.930 --> 00:47:46.163
Is that what it is?

573
00:47:46.164 --> 00:47:48.232
We like to call it sauerkraut.

574
00:47:48.233 --> 00:47:50.400
- This is sauerkraut?
- Yep.

575
00:47:50.401 --> 00:47:51.835
You've never had
sauerkraut before?

576
00:47:51.836 --> 00:47:53.370
No. I haven't.
It's a little hard

577
00:47:53.371 --> 00:47:55.439
to come by
in the Pacific States.

578
00:47:55.440 --> 00:47:56.540
Colleen Meyer said

579
00:47:56.541 --> 00:47:59.076
that the Japs eat dogs
in the Pacific States.

580
00:47:59.077 --> 00:48:00.945
- Is that true?
- Jennifer.

581
00:48:00.946 --> 00:48:03.747
No. The Japanese do not
eat dogs. I promise.

582
00:48:03.748 --> 00:48:05.283
What about cats?

583
00:48:06.551 --> 00:48:07.652
Occasionally.

584
00:48:09.955 --> 00:48:10.955
Kidding.

585
00:48:17.695 --> 00:48:19.063
Excuse me.

586
00:48:27.805 --> 00:48:29.673
You know what I did
hear. girls...

587
00:48:29.674 --> 00:48:31.977
That they eat raw fish.

588
00:48:33.779 --> 00:48:35.212
Yes?

589
00:48:35.213 --> 00:48:36.982
Joe: Did you know?

590
00:48:39.617 --> 00:48:41.352
Just tell me the truth.

591
00:48:42.520 --> 00:48:44.654
It's good to hear from you. Joe.

592
00:48:44.655 --> 00:48:46.457
How's Berlin?

593
00:48:48.259 --> 00:48:50.228
Did you know I'm Lebensborn?

594
00:48:53.731 --> 00:48:55.133
Yes. I knew.

595
00:49:04.609 --> 00:49:05.809
Why didn't you tell me?

596
00:49:05.810 --> 00:49:07.244
It wasn't my place.

597
00:49:07.245 --> 00:49:10.647
You mean because
it didn't benefit you.

598
00:49:10.648 --> 00:49:13.017
That's the only reason
you ever do anything.

599
00:49:13.018 --> 00:49:14.218
isn't it?

600
00:49:14.219 --> 00:49:17.087
What I did I did for you. Joe.

601
00:49:17.088 --> 00:49:19.423
You have a great future
ahead of you.

602
00:49:19.424 --> 00:49:21.491
And you thought I'd
be useful to you.

603
00:49:21.492 --> 00:49:23.827
Well. you're important
to me. Joe.

604
00:49:23.828 --> 00:49:26.430
I won't deny that.

605
00:49:26.431 --> 00:49:28.066
We're done.

606
00:50:00.331 --> 00:50:02.300
Helen:
Everything okay. honey?

607
00:50:03.734 --> 00:50:05.403
Everything's fine.

608
00:50:47.178 --> 00:50:50.414
Mr. Washington.
Right on time.

609
00:50:50.415 --> 00:50:52.749
You about ready to go.
Mr. A?

610
00:50:52.750 --> 00:50:54.451
There's a stack inside.

611
00:50:54.452 --> 00:50:57.487
Would you bring it out
for me. please?

612
00:50:57.488 --> 00:51:00.724
Don't want to get that nice
suit all rumpled up. huh?

613
00:51:00.725 --> 00:51:01.726
Mm-mm.

614
00:51:17.542 --> 00:51:18.643
There's a...

615
00:51:19.610 --> 00:51:21.678
There's a strong smell inside.

616
00:51:21.679 --> 00:51:23.848
- You noticed.
- Like gas.

617
00:51:30.621 --> 00:51:32.756
That's the smell
of leaving. Lem.

618
00:51:32.757 --> 00:51:34.425
the smell of moving on.

619
00:51:35.860 --> 00:51:37.262
What about the rest of them?

620
00:51:43.268 --> 00:51:47.205
Nothing like a good
spring cleaning.

621
00:53:49.594 --> 00:53:50.995
Noriaki?

622
00:53:57.735 --> 00:53:59.002
Wow.

623
00:53:59.003 --> 00:54:00.571
You're back.

624
00:54:02.740 --> 00:54:05.309
Why do you talk to me this way?

625
00:54:05.310 --> 00:54:06.776
Why do you dishonor Mom?

626
00:54:06.777 --> 00:54:08.044
Noriaki. please.

627
00:54:08.045 --> 00:54:09.447
No. he needs to hear this.

628
00:54:11.349 --> 00:54:13.717
The world's about
to come to an end.

629
00:54:13.718 --> 00:54:16.320
and you disappear
on another one
of your benders?

630
00:54:16.321 --> 00:54:19.323
I did not do what you say.

631
00:54:30.368 --> 00:54:32.603
Woman: Nori?

632
00:54:35.340 --> 00:54:36.941
He's back. honey.

633
00:54:38.976 --> 00:54:40.345
Oh.

634
00:54:45.249 --> 00:54:47.517
Thank God you're all right.

